Image Generation Prompt: Canvas tote bag, minimalist design, blooming flowers
Steps:
```html
  1. Gather materials: A plain canvas tote bag and waste materials suitable for creating a floral design (e.g., fabric scraps, plastic bottle caps, etc.).
  2. Design the floral pattern: Sketch a floral bouquet design on paper, considering the size and shape of the tote bag. Alternatively, print a floral design onto transfer paper.
  3. Prepare waste materials: Cut, shape, or otherwise modify your waste materials to create individual floral elements (petals, leaves, stems) according to your design.
  4. Assemble the design: Arrange the waste material elements onto the tote bag to mimic your floral design. Secure them using fabric glue or stitching.
  5. Finishing touches: Once the design is secure, consider adding embellishments or sealant to protect the artwork and make it more durable.
```
